	<tr>
		<td width="150" align="left" valign="top" class="row1"><span class="name"><a name="76309"></a><b>polad1</b></span><br /><span class="postdetails">
		
		<br />Joined: 10 Nov 2003<br />Posts: 239</span></td>
		<td class="row1" width="100%" height="28" valign="top">

		<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
			<tr>
			<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td width="100%"><a href="viewtopic.php?p=76309&amp;sid=a143b8d25b5cebafd65ac72d231635ff#76309"><img src="templates/eqluclin/images/icon_minipost.gif" width="12" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" border="0" /></a><span class="postdetails">Posted: Thu Jul 22, 2004 6:42 pm<span class="gen">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; &nbsp;Post subject: Re: Bugman gets a new job</span></td>
				<td width="30%" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap" align="right"> <a href="posting.php?mode=quote&amp;p=76309&amp;sid=a143b8d25b5cebafd65ac72d231635ff"><img src="templates/eqluclin/images/lang_english/icon_quote.gif" alt="Reply with quote" title="Reply with quote" border="0" /></a>   </td></tr></table></td>
			</tr>
			<tr><td colspan="2"><hr /></td></tr>
			<tr><td colspan="2">
				<div class="postbody">
				</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Tangurena wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote"> If it is a <span style="font-style: italic">Perry Stop</span> they <span style="text-decoration: underline">can</span> stop and  frisk you, they only need probable cause.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Terry (not Perry) stops do not automatically entail frisking.  An officer must show reasonable suspicion that the suspect they stop under Terry is armed and dangerous.  They can only pat you down for weapons and not contraband, <span style="font-weight: bold">if</span> they have reasonable, probable cause to do so.  If they feel the outline of a pipe (a bowl) in your pants, and they remove it, it's not likely admissible in court as evidence because a marijuana pipe can't be reasonbly confused with a weapon or something the could contain a weapon.
<br />

<br />
"Lunging distance" items (things within reach of a suspect) can also be searched, if they're not locked (a suspect wouldn't have time to unlock and use the contents before he was stopped by the officers).
<br />

<br />
If an officer was walking down the street and locked eyes with you coming from the other direction and you run off, if he chases you down and finds contraband on you, most likely none of it will be admissible because it was a bad stop.  He had no indication of suspicion that you were committing a crime or about to commit one.  Running from the police is not a sign of guilt.<br />
				<span class="gensmall"></span><br />
				</div>
			</td></tr>
		</table>
		</td>
	</tr>
